🚀 Devops Project 03: Launch Your Own LAMP Stack Web App on AWS!**

Lightsail:
Amazon Lightsail is a AWS service easy-to-use virtual private server (VPS) instances, containers, storage, databases,more at a cost-effective monthly price.
The main benefit is it's simplified setup and management processes allow businesses to quickly deploy and maintain their applications.

LAMP Stack:
A LAMP stack is a bundle of four different software technologies that developers use to build websites and web applications. 
LAMP is an acronym for the operating system, Linux; the web server, Apache; the database server, MySQL; and the programming language, PHP.


🌐 **Step 1: Set Up AWS Account**
Sign up for an AWS account at [AWS Sign-Up](https://aws.amazon.com/) to get started.

☁️ **Step 2: Access AWS Management Console**
Log in to the [AWS Management Console](https://aws.amazon.com/console/) to start building.

🖥️ **Step 3: Launch EC2 Instance**
Follow the tutorial to launch an EC2 instance with your preferred Linux distribution.

🔗 **Step 4: Connect to EC2 Instance**
Use SSH to connect to your instance using the provided key pair.

🚀 **Step 5: Install Apache Web Server**
Update and install Apache to set up the foundation for your web app.

🔒 **Step 6: Secure MySQL Installation**
Securely install MySQL and run the security script for protection.

💻 **Step 7: Install PHP**
Install PHP and necessary modules for Apache to enable server-side scripting.

🚧 **Step 8: Create Simple PHP File**
Test your LAMP stack by creating a simple PHP file in the Apache document root.

🌐 **Step 9: Access Web App**
Open your browser, go to your EC2 instance's IP address, and witness your PHP info page.

📁 **Step 10: Create Your Web Application**
Upload your web app files to the server and configure settings as needed.

🔒 **Step 11: Configure Security Groups**
Ensure that your EC2 instance's security group allows inbound traffic on ports 80 and 443.

🌐 **Step 12: Domain Configuration (Optional)**
For a personalized touch, configure your domain to point to your EC2 instance.

🔄 **Step 13: Regular Maintenance**
Perform routine tasks like updating packages, backing up your database, and monitoring logs.


🚀 Reference:[AWS LAMP Web App Tutorial](https://aws.amazon.com/getting-started/hands-on/launch-lamp-web-app/)
